title: Getting the message "Not replacing existing, living, managed instance with new object."
body:
I'm running locally on Windows and I find that if I run my application multithreaded, I get a lot of the debugger output:

Not replacing existing, living, managed instance with new object.

I don't seem to get this if I only run with a single thread. I haven't tracked down the reproduction any more than that yet.

The source code seems to point to this line:

https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/blob/master/binding/Binding/SKObject.cs#L124

But I don't yet understand when `RegisterHandle` gets called.

Is this a harmless message? Is there something I should change to prevent this from occurring?
